Analyses                            High resolution (1/4 degree) Temperature and Salinity   Analyses of the World's Oceans   The 1/4° grid climatological mean fields of temperature and salinity for the annual, seasonal, and monthly  time periods were calculated using objective analysis techniques which were basically the same as those detailed in the World Ocean Atlas 2001  temperature (Stephens et al, 2002) and World Ocean Atlas 2001 salinity (Boyer et al, 2002)  for the 1° grid climatological mean fields,  with differences as described in the  methods  ( PDF, 0.5 MB ). For each   gridpoint, the gp file contains the number of surrounding gridpoints   within the smallest radius of influence for the objective analysis   which contain mean values.
